Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of graph rewriting systems to model biochemical systems, which can be considered as a type of control system. 
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems): The paper also mentions the dynamics of the model being driven by rules and strategies, which falls under the category of dynamical systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of graph rewriting systems as a modelling tool can also be relevant to the field of artificial intelligence, particularly in the area of knowledge representation and reasoning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper describes the development of a visual and interactive tool for graph rewriting, which can be considered as a programming language for modelling systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): While not the main focus of the paper, the use of graph rewriting systems can also be relevant to machine learning, particularly in the area of graph-based models and algorithms.
